		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Host desecration</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>Host <a href="/wiki/Desecration" title="Desecration">desecration</a></b> is a form of <a href="/wiki/Sacrilege" title="Sacrilege">sacrilege</a> in <a href="/wiki/Christianity" title="Christianity">Christianity</a>, involving the mistreatment or malicious use of a consecrated <a href="/wiki/Host_(Holy_Communion)" title="Host (Holy Communion)" class="mw-redirect">Host</a>, or communion bread. Throughout history, a number of groups have been accused of desecrating hosts; because of the religious importance of the consecrated wafer, the accusation is one of metaphysical evil and hostility towards God.</p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
